| \`typography.body.md\` | typography | semantic | Inter 1rem/1.5 400 | Default body copy. |
| \`typography.heading.lg\` | typography | semantic | Inter 2rem/1.2 700 | Page and section headings. |
| \`typography.label.sm\` | typography | semantic | Inter 0.875rem/1.4 500 | Form labels and button text. |

## Components

### Alert
_Communicate an important, contextual message._

- **Variants:** info, danger
- **States:** default
- **Tokens:** background=\`color.surface\`, borderColor=\`color.border\`, color=\`color.text\`, padding=\`spacing.3\`, radius=\`radius.md\`

**Do:**
- Use for contextual, in-page messages tied to a task.
**Avoid:**
- Don't use for transient notifications — use a Toast (later).
**Accessibility:**
- color.text on color.surface = 17.44:1 (AA pass)
\`\`\`tsx
<Alert tone="danger">Something went wrong</Alert>
\`\`\`

### Badge
_Label or annotate with a small status token._

- **Variants:** default, danger
- **States:** default
- **Tokens:** background=\`color.primary\`, color=\`color.textOnPrimary\`, paddingX=\`spacing.2\`, radius=\`radius.sm\`

**Do:**
- Use for short status labels (1-2 words).
**Avoid:**
- Don't use Badge as a button — it is not interactive.
**Accessibility:**
- color.textOnPrimary on color.primary = 7.79:1 (AA pass)
\`\`\`tsx
<Badge>New</Badge>
\`\`\`

### Button
_Trigger a single, clear action._

- **Variants:** primary, secondary, ghost
- **States:** default, hover, focus, disabled, loading
- **Tokens:** background=\`color.primary\`, color=\`color.textOnPrimary\`, font=\`typography.label.sm\`, gap=\`spacing.1\`, paddingX=\`spacing.3\`, paddingY=\`spacing.2\`, radius=\`radius.md\`

**Do:**
- Use for the single primary action on a screen.
**Avoid:**
- Don't use for navigation — use a Link.
- Don't place two primary Buttons side by side.
**Accessibility:**
- color.textOnPrimary on color.primary = 7.79:1 (AA pass)
\`\`\`tsx
<Button variant="primary">Save</Button>
\`\`\`

### Card
_Group related content on a surface._

- **Variants:** default
- **States:** default
- **Tokens:** background=\`color.surface\`, padding=\`spacing.4\`, radius=\`radius.lg\`, shadow=\`shadow.sm\`

**Do:**
- Use to group related content into a scannable unit.
**Avoid:**
- Don't nest cards more than one level deep.
**Accessibility:**
- color.text on color.surface = 17.44:1 (AA pass)
\`\`\`tsx
<Card>…</Card>
\`\`\`

### Dialog
_Interrupt the flow for a focused, modal task._

- **Variants:** default
- **States:** open, closed
- **Tokens:** background=\`color.surface\`, padding=\`spacing.6\`, radius=\`radius.lg\`, shadow=\`shadow.md\`

**Do:**
- Use for a focused decision or task that blocks the underlying page.
**Avoid:**
- Don't stack multiple Dialogs.
- Don't use for non-blocking info.
**Accessibility:**
- color.text on color.surface = 17.44:1 (AA pass)
\`\`\`tsx
<Dialog open>…</Dialog>
\`\`\`

### Input
_Collect a single line of text from the user._

- **Variants:** default, error
- **States:** default, focus, disabled
- **Tokens:** background=\`color.surface\`, borderColor=\`color.border\`, color=\`color.text\`, paddingX=\`spacing.3\`, paddingY=\`spacing.2\`, radius=\`radius.sm\`

**Do:**
- Always pair with a visible label.
**Avoid:**
- Don't use placeholder text as the only label.
**Accessibility:**
- color.text on color.surface = 17.44:1 (AA pass)
- color.border on color.surface = 1.66:1 (AA fail)
\`\`\`tsx
<Input aria-label="Email" />
\`\`\`

## Patterns

### Auth form
_Let a returning user sign in._
- **Usage:** Use on dedicated sign-in pages, centered on the screen.
- **Uses:** Button, Input

**Do:**
- Use one primary Button (Sign in) and label every Input.
**Avoid:**
- Don't add more than the fields needed to authenticate.

### Empty state
_Explain why a view is empty and offer the next action._
- **Usage:** Use when a list/collection has no items yet.
- **Uses:** Button

**Do:**
- Explain the empty state and give one clear primary action.
**Avoid:**
- Don't show an empty state that looks like an error.

### Pricing card
_Present a single plan and its call to action._
- **Usage:** Use in a row of comparable plans.
- **Uses:** Badge, Button, Card

**Do:**
- Highlight at most one recommended plan with the primary Button.
**Avoid:**
- Don't overload the card with more than ~5 feature lines.

### Settings section
_Group a set of related settings with a save action._
- **Usage:** Use within a settings page, one section per concern.
- **Uses:** Button, Card, Input

**Do:**
- Group related fields and provide a single save action per section.
**Avoid:**
- Don't auto-save destructive changes without confirmation.

"
